<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 23 at 9:22PM EST  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>Locally dense fog expected through 200 AM...
Patchy dense ground fog has developed over portions of the
Piedmont including the Yadkin Valley. A few locations including
Albemarle, Lexington, and Siler City have been reporting
visibilities of less than a quarter of a mile. Locally dense fog
can be expected through midnight to 200 AM Thursday. A few
locations may experience near zero visibilities. The fog should
lift or improve after midnight as clouds increase and near
surface winds increase with a cold frontal passage.
Motorists are urged to slow down and take plenty of time while
traveling. Highly variable visibilities ranging from unlimited to
less than 50 feet over relatively areas will create a hazard
until all the visibilities improve later tonight.</description>
